TableContextTimeStampBeforeTable: {23502=NDC 0781-1785-01 bottles of 100 tablets, 22957=NDC 0781-1787-13 unit dose packages of 100 tablets, 23017=NDC 0781-1787-10 bottles of 1000 tablets, 887=NDC 0781-1789-01, 22651=NDC 0781-1789-01 bottles of 100 tablets, 22709=NDC 0781-1789-60 bottles of 60 tablets, 23134=NDC 0781-1787-60 bottles of 60 tablets, 2899=NDC 0781-1785-01, 22533=NDC 0781-1789-10 bottles of 1000 tablets, 22592=NDC 0781-1789-05 bottles of 500 tablets, 23383=NDC 0781-1785-13 unit dose packages of 100 tablets, 23560=NDC 0781-1785-60 bottles of 60 tablets, 84800=Diclofenac sodium is a faintly yellowish white to light beige, virtually odorless, slightly hygroscopic crystalline powder. It is freely soluble in methanol, soluble in ethanol, sparingly soluble in water and practically insoluble in chloroform and in dilute acid. The n-octanol/water partition coefficient is 13.4 at pH 7.4 and 1545 at pH 5.2. Diclofenac sodium has a dissociation constant (pKa) of 4.0 ± 0.2 at 25°C in water., 23076=NDC 0781-1787-01 bottles of 100 tablets, 94252=0781-1787-01, 23443=NDC 0781-1785-10 bottles of 1000 tablets, 1893=NDC 0781-1787-01, 3925=Call your doctor for medical advice about side effects.
